result.name: A Plus Kitchen

reviews.text: A mordern cha chan tang in Shek Tong Tsui area
An okay Hong Kong style tea restaurant. Price is reasonable.

The name of this restaurant is A+ but it gets a D- rating from me.  The $88 clay pot rice with abalone and dried shrimp 讚記煲仔飯 was really attractive in picture.  When it came, the two abalones were so small (20mm) and we could smell the burnt rice.  The lady 亞嬸 who served it immediately said to leave it covered.  I said I could smell burnt rice.  She sarcastically said “You haven’t had clay pot rice before?  This is how it is.”  你未食過煲仔飯咩？煲仔飯係咁㗎”。The chef burnt the rice and couldn’t cook it any further.  That’s why they told us to leave it covered to simmer the rice.  I noticed she didn’t say the same thing to other tables ordering similar.  We scooped up what we can eat.  We turned the bottom up and half the thick layer of rice at the bottom was blackened.  We didn’t complain to the owner to cause a scene because we know we will never return to this place.
The breakfast is good
Large space in HK, nice food
